  <div class="cities">
  <h2>About</h2>
    <p>Padding is a spcing element used in the INSIDE of the object.</p>
   
    <p>
    
    Definition and Usage
An element's padding is the space between its content and its border.
    </p>
<p>The padding property is a shorthand property for:
    </p>
    <p>padding-top</p>
    <p>padding-right</p>
    <p>padding-bottom</p>
    <p>padding-left</p>
  
<p>Note: Padding creates extra space within an element, while margin creates extra space around an element.
    </p>
<p>This property can have from one to four values.
    </p>
   
<P>If the padding property has four values:
  </p>
<p>padding:10px 5px 15px 20px;</p>
<p>top padding is 10px</p>
<p>right padding is 5px</p>
<p>bottom padding is 15px</p>
<p>left padding is 20px</p>
<p>If the padding property has three values:</p>
<div>
<p>padding:10px 5px 15px;</p>
<p>top padding is 10px</p>
<p>right and left padding are 5px</p>
<p>bottom padding is 15px</p>
<p>If the padding property has two values:</p>

<p>padding:10px 5px;</p>
<p>top and bottom padding are 10px</p>
<p>right and left padding are 5px</p>
<p>If the padding property has one value:</p>

<p>padding:10px;</p>
<p>all four paddings are 10px</p>
<p>Note: Negative values are not allowed.</p>
</p>
</div>
